item.description:
@cooper wrote:

Since when is a plus sign the same as “to”? You still haven’t proven that he won’t choose Cowie`s [the only way to prove it would be to ask the poster himself]
Green:

Black:

Your conclusion that I “must” be colour blind is wrong. First of all, I am not, and second of all, there are many other factors that could be involved. My screen could be outdated and dim, creating the illusion of those two colours, etc. Even if the colours weren’t there, there is still no way for you to prove I am 100% colour blind.

tl;dr - don’t use absolutes like must when you have no proof on the subject matter [in this case me being colour blind or not]
